post_cb({"27084605": {"ParentId": "27084470", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>Both code-snippets induce undefined behavior if <code>int</code> has 32 bit or less. [expr.shift]/1:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_27084470_27084605_0\">The behavior is undefined if the right operand is negative, or greater\n  than or equal to the length in bits of the promoted left operand.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Hence an implementation is not in any way obliged to provide consistent results.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "3647361", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "27084605", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2014-11-23T01:29:33.807", "LastActivityDate": "2014-11-23T01:29:33.807"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_27084470_27084605_0": {"section_id": 6146, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 13}}, "n3337": {"so_27084470_27084605_0": {"section_id": 5909, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 13}}, "n4659": {"so_27084470_27084605_0": {"section_id": 7642, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 13}}}, "27084470": {"CommentCount": "3", "ViewCount": "61", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "3647361", "CreationDate": "2014-11-23T01:09:32.213", "LastActivityDate": "2016-03-18T10:39:57.597", "Title": "Why the following two programs yield different outputs? (C++, bit operation, VS 2012)", "AcceptedAnswerId": "27084605", "LastEditDate": "2016-03-18T10:39:57.597", "Id": "27084470", "Score": "2", "Body": "<p>Program 1:</p>\n<pre><code>int x = 4 ^ (4&gt;&gt;32);\ncout &lt;&lt; x &lt;&lt; endl;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Output is 4</p>\n<p>Program 2:</p>\n<pre><code>int x = 4;\nint y = x ^ (x&gt;&gt;32);\ncout &lt;&lt; y &lt;&lt; endl;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Output is 0</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><visual-studio-2012><language-lawyer><bit><undefined-behavior>", "OwnerUserId": "2429379", "AnswerCount": "1"}});